c2bbd0f8aea01f74347b24919f909c2b597be4fa61bcc227346d10","event_uuid":"b87c5dd8-e214-472b-88c7-1c75635913dd","position":{"commit_sha":"dbee13411b98d91b3416d7904bee0b1133b3467f","position":"1784442780632339001-b87c5dd8-e214-472b-88c7-1c75635913dd"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"d56796339eb0090563b7a4104d15dac133056ba179d8e7977e08afc3ed6692a1","event_uuid":"f66c9dea-8412-4f72-a075-fb1f45d0e58e","position":{"commit_sha":"37741cb990042d5ff588ec88a4db031620a35311","position":"1784442959898005422-f66c9dea-8412-4f72-a075-fb1f45d0e58e"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416750080483001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"507c666d-e89f-431f-a063-b66ac2d0ad1c","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a"},{"link_uuid":"9e1046a1-d135-4b02-a9bc-9d14d4f82e6f","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"}],"description":"## What\nRead-only derivations over the durable ticket event store (including compaction-retired `.retired` events) for the agent-process metrics that have a **clean, verifiable event signature today**: attempts-per-ticket, first-pass verification rate, rework at 7/30 days, reopen-recovery, and revert-linked recovery. Metrics whose signal has no reliable event vocabulary yet (escalation, cross-agent handoff/handoff-failure) are explicitly **out of scope for this ticket** and report `Unavailable` from the registry until a later ticket adds their instrumentation — this ticket does not claim them.\n\n## Data-access ground truth (HYBRID — compiled state where one terminal value suffices; raw events where per-event data is needed)\n`reduce_ticket(..., include_retired=True)` returns a **single collapsed terminal-state dict, NOT an ordered event sequence** (`src/rebar/reducer/_api.py:127`), and there is **no** public ordered-event API. So this reader is a deliberate **hybrid**, and each metric states which source it uses:\n- **Metrics needing per-event or multi-occurrence data (attempts, rework windows, reopen counts)** read the **raw event files**, because compiled state keeps only the *current* value (e.g. one `claimed_session`, one `last_reopened_at`). To read them, **reuse the existing reducer helpers — do NOT reinvent file-listing/sorting/retired-handling**: sort with `rebar.reducer._sort.event_sort_key` (the authoritative chronological key — plain `sorted()` is NOT relied upon), include/exclude compaction-retired events via `rebar.reducer._cache.is_active_event` / `RETIRED_SUFFIX`, and skip `*-SNAPSHOT.json`. Resolve the ticket dir via `rebar.config.tracker_dir(repo_root)` + `rebar._engine_support.resolver.resolve_ticket_dir_name`.\n- **Metrics for which a single terminal value is sufficient (first_pass_rate via `last_reopened_at`-absent, revert_recovery via `reverts[]`)** read **compiled state** from `reduce_ticket` — simpler and correct, since only the terminal fact (\"was it ever reopened\", \"does it carry a substantive revert\") is needed.\n\n`Verified -1` does **not** exist anywhere in the event schema and is not used (the store's verdict vocabulary is PASS/FAIL/BLOCK plus the `gate_error_v1` ERROR).\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py` — new: read-only functions taking `(repo_root, since, until)`, registered into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`. Each returns `None` (→ c085 `Unavailable`) when the range yields no qualifying tickets; a genuine measured zero returns `0`.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` — new.\n\n## Metric definitions (each names its source: RAW = raw event files via the reused helpers; STATE = compiled `reduce_ticket`)\n- **attempts_per_ticket** [RAW] — distinct claim sessions: read the ticket's event files (sorted via `event_sort_key`, retired included via `is_active_event`), filter to `*-STATUS.json` on the `open→in_progress` edge (`data.current_status==\"open\" and data.status==\"in_progress\"`), collect distinct `data.session` (stamped by `_stamp_session`, `txn.py:56-76`). Compiled state keeps only the *current* `claimed_session`, so raw events are required to count multiple attempts.\n- **first_pass_rate** [STATE] — fraction of closed tickets in range that were never reopened: `state[\"last_reopened_at\"]` absent (it is set only on a `closed→open` edge, `_processors.py:304-310`, so its absence is a sufficient terminal signal).\n- **rework_within_days(n)** for n∈{7,30} [RAW] — tickets with a `closed→open` STATUS edge followed by a later `→closed` edge within n days, measured from raw STATUS event `timestamp`s (multiple edges → raw required).\n- **reopen_recovery** [RAW] — count of tickets with ≥1 `closed→open` STATUS edge in range (raw scan; a full count needs every edge, not just the terminal `last_reopened_at`).\n- **revert_recovery** [STATE] — tickets whose reduced `state[\"reverts\"]` (records `{target_event_uuid, target_event_type, timestamp, ...}`, `_processors.py:452-462`) contains a revert whose `target_event_type` is `STATUS` or `COMMITS` — a substantive revert, not a revert of a COMMENT/LINK. The terminal `reverts[]` list is sufficient, so compiled state is used.\n\n## Approach\nEverything is structurally witnessed and read-only — no new emission. HLC filename timestamps are real wall-clock ns, so date-range bucketing is exact. `source=\"structural\"`, `confidence=\"high\"` (authoritative). Compaction-retired events are included so history survives compaction.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp store; craft raw event files directly with known timestamps/sessions): a ticket with two distinct `open→in_progress` sessions yields `attempts_per_ticket==2`; a `closed→open→closed` 3 days apart counts in `rework_within_days(7)` but not a 10-day gap; a ticket closed and never reopened counts toward `first_pass_rate`; a ticket with a REVERT of a STATUS event is counted by `revert_recovery` while a ticket with only a COMMENT-revert is not; retired (`*.retired`) events are still counted.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_event_metrics.py` passes: a fixture ticket claimed by two distinct sessions yields `attempts_per_ticket == 2` (exact), and a single-session ticket yields `1`.\n- [ ] a `closed→open→closed` transition 3 days apart is counted in `rework_within_days(7)` and NOT in a variant 10 days apart — both asserted.\n- [ ] `revert_recovery` counts a ticket whose `reverts` targets a STATUS event and does NOT count one whose only revert targets a COMMENT — asserted (proves the target_event_type filter).\n- [ ] a metric over an empty range returns `None` so `evaluate()` reports `Unavailable`; a populated range with zero qualifying events returns `0` (measured zero) — both asserted.\n- [ ] the metrics register into `src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` with `source=\"structural\"` and are authoritative — asserted.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py","reason":"event-derivation readers"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d"],["depends_on","c085-6d11-d68d-422a"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"3d4dc82e-bdc9-4c12-8032-f942b0f9af53","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"18e6-4bfb-1dcf-4a37","ticket_type":"task","title":"Event-derivation readers (agent-process metrics over the durable event store)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["765028e1-70ce-4a96-8242-87e73bea5c0b","1f0b3d5d-7dae-4c3f-ac38-7c8d70674002","507c666d-e89f-431f-a063-b66ac2d0ad1c","9e1046a1-d135-4b02-a9bc-9d14d4f82e6f","413bffb0-0c74-4993-bbfd-18c97a51b524","bc64351a-9cb2-4818-a6e7-abeba9b85fc1","8ce781ef-2203-4d1b-89ce-81ebc4d6658c","3d4dc82e-bdc9-4c12-8032-f942b0f9af53","b87c5dd8-e214-472b-88c7-1c75635913dd","f66c9dea-8412-4f72-a075-fb1f45d0e58e"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784442959898005423,"uuid":"5a1ca1bd-5bbe-47f7-a382-a41bb38be039"}